1
00:01:42,035 --> 00:01:42,836
Are you okay?

2
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:51,478
Take me back to Mom's.

3
00:02:13,733 --> 00:02:14,667
Your favorite walnut buns.

4
00:02:15,368 --> 00:02:15,969
And siu mai.

5
00:02:18,705 --> 00:02:19,439
And some sour fruit.

6
00:02:21,608 --> 00:02:22,275
Sister Xiaoran.

7
00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:24,210
Next time, help me talk to Yi.

8
00:02:24,677 --> 00:02:25,512
I've told him.

9
00:02:25,645 --> 00:02:26,679
These red spider lilies—

10
00:02:26,913 --> 00:02:27,814
he needs to water them for me.

11
00:02:28,281 --> 00:02:29,149
But he just won't.

12
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:30,884
You're counting on him?

13
00:02:34,087 --> 00:02:34,654
Fair point.

14
00:02:35,188 --> 00:02:36,289
I've never seen anyone so lazy.

15
00:02:42,395 --> 00:02:43,096
Do you think

16
00:02:43,096 --> 00:02:43,796
he's watching me right now?

17
00:02:44,964 --> 00:02:46,432
Probably not right now.

18
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:48,468
He's likely in surgery.

19
00:02:49,269 --> 00:02:50,603
But he'll watch the replay. The replay.

20
00:02:54,574 --> 00:02:55,508
So annoying.

21
00:02:56,576 --> 00:02:57,610
Always monitoring us.

22
00:02:59,112 --> 00:02:59,679
Peeping Tom.

23
00:03:03,983 --> 00:03:04,484
Still watching?

24
00:03:46,025 --> 00:03:46,392
Come in.

25
00:03:49,295 --> 00:03:49,729
President Wang.

26
00:03:50,763 --> 00:03:51,230
Xiaofeng.

27
00:03:51,931 --> 00:03:52,999
What brings you here so early?

28
00:03:53,466 --> 00:03:54,133
What is it?

29
00:03:56,436 --> 00:03:57,804
There's an eighteen-year-old patient

30
00:03:58,171 --> 00:03:59,472
who needs an artificial heart implant.

31
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:01,608
I'd like to report it and ask for approval.

32
00:04:02,675 --> 00:04:03,409
Sheng Nian said

33
00:04:03,943 --> 00:04:04,310
he'd be coming

34
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:05,245
to discuss the same case.

35
00:04:05,845 --> 00:04:06,879
I'll call him in now.

36
00:04:07,113 --> 00:04:08,047
You can explain it together.

37
00:04:10,717 --> 00:04:12,185
Ask Director Sheng to come to my office.

38
00:04:17,890 --> 00:04:18,925
Which of you wants to go first?

39
00:04:22,495 --> 00:04:23,229
The surgery is imminent,

40
00:04:23,863 --> 00:04:24,864
and this will be Dongli's first

41
00:04:24,864 --> 00:04:25,932
artificial heart procedure.

42
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:27,634
I still think

43
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:28,568
we need another discussion

44
00:04:28,801 --> 00:04:30,303
about the device selection.

45
00:04:31,671 --> 00:04:32,171
Director Zhou,

46
00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:33,840
what are you still worried about?

47
00:04:35,575 --> 00:04:36,042
President Wang,

48
00:04:36,409 --> 00:04:37,644
you're an expert in this field.

49
00:04:37,877 --> 00:04:38,678
During the consultation,

50
00:04:38,711 --> 00:04:40,613
I made everything very clear.

51
00:04:40,847 --> 00:04:41,547
I will personally

52
00:04:41,814 --> 00:04:42,749
perform this surgery.

53
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:44,651
So the choice of device

54
00:04:44,984 --> 00:04:45,785
is mine to make.

55
00:04:50,757 --> 00:04:53,593
Since Director Sheng is the lead surgeon,

56
00:04:54,694 --> 00:04:56,562
we should respect his plan.

57
00:04:59,265 --> 00:04:59,732
President Wang,

58
00:05:00,166 --> 00:05:01,734
is there anything else?

59
00:05:02,335 --> 00:05:02,769
Since Director Zhou

60
00:05:03,302 --> 00:05:04,570
is here today,

61
00:05:04,771 --> 00:05:06,439
I'd also like to request

62
00:05:06,673 --> 00:05:08,474
that although this patient

63
00:05:08,474 --> 00:05:10,109
was first admitted by Cardiology,

64
00:05:10,343 --> 00:05:11,911
for easier follow-up management,

65
00:05:12,812 --> 00:05:13,746
he be transferred directly

66
00:05:13,846 --> 00:05:14,614
to Cardiac Surgery.

67
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:18,551
The Heart Center's usual rule

68
00:05:19,052 --> 00:05:19,919
is that the admitting department remains responsible.

69
00:05:20,586 --> 00:05:21,888
A patient admitted by Cardiology

70
00:05:22,288 --> 00:05:23,189
naturally remains ours.

71
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:25,591
This is a special case.

72
00:05:26,025 --> 00:05:27,760
Artificial heart implantation is highly specialized

73
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:28,528
and fundamentally

74
00:05:28,561 --> 00:05:30,029
led by Cardiac Surgery.

75
00:05:30,196 --> 00:05:31,431
We're doing ninety percent of the work,

76
00:05:31,798 --> 00:05:32,999
yet the patient remains in your department.

77
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:33,866
That doesn't seem appropriate.

78
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:35,568
From the moment he was admitted,

79
00:05:35,735 --> 00:05:36,803
whether it was assessment, diagnosis,

80
00:05:36,869 --> 00:05:37,770
medication, or treatment planning,

81
00:05:37,804 --> 00:05:39,005
I handled everything personally.

82
00:05:39,072 --> 00:05:39,806
But now we've reached

83
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:40,807
the critical stage.

84
00:05:40,973 --> 00:05:42,175
What matters is who controls

85
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:42,842
the core technology.

86
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:44,343
What matters now

87
00:05:45,878 --> 00:05:47,213
is treating the patient

88
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:49,282
and ensuring his safety.

89
00:05:49,649 --> 00:05:50,717
The surgery hasn't even begun,

90
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:51,884
and you two department heads

91
00:05:51,918 --> 00:05:53,052
are already fighting over credit.

92
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:54,320
Don't you think

93
00:05:54,353 --> 00:05:55,054
this looks ugly?

94
00:05:57,423 --> 00:05:57,924
President Wang,

95
00:05:58,891 --> 00:06:00,326
all performance credit can go to Cardiac Surgery,

96
00:06:01,227 --> 00:06:02,795
but the patient must remain in Cardiology.

97
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:07,867
Listen carefully, both of you.

98
00:06:08,668 --> 00:06:09,602
This is our hospital's

99
00:06:10,570 --> 00:06:11,204
first

100
00:06:12,004 --> 00:06:13,106
artificial heart procedure.

101
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:14,907
The hospital's requirement is

102
00:06:15,308 --> 00:06:16,509
a smooth and successful operation.

103
00:06:17,543 --> 00:06:18,444
Everything else

104
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:19,712
can wait.

105
00:06:47,206 --> 00:06:47,774
Looks like

106
00:06:47,774 --> 00:06:48,908
the anniversary is coming again.

107
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:50,109
They've already hung the huge banners.

108
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:52,645
Isn't your school celebrating

109
00:06:52,678 --> 00:06:54,714
its 130th anniversary this year?

110
00:06:55,348 --> 00:06:56,849
I won't attend this time.

111
00:06:59,385 --> 00:07:00,052
I heard

112
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:02,054
the boy with

113
00:07:02,121 --> 00:07:02,889
left ventricular noncompaction

114
00:07:03,322 --> 00:07:04,824
agreed to an artificial heart.

115
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:05,825
He did.

116
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,595
Then is it confirmed

117
00:07:09,629 --> 00:07:11,864
Director Sheng will do it himself?

118
00:07:16,502 --> 00:07:17,603
If Director Sheng wants to operate,

119
00:07:17,637 --> 00:07:18,204
who would dare stop him?

120
00:07:18,504 --> 00:07:19,772
That makes sense.

121
00:07:20,673 --> 00:07:21,607
Maybe I've just

122
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:22,408
gotten used to it.

123
00:07:22,909 --> 00:07:24,544
Ever since Lin Yi

124
00:07:24,544 --> 00:07:25,444
came to Dongli,

125
00:07:25,645 --> 00:07:27,647
whenever there's a pioneering procedure,

126
00:07:27,814 --> 00:07:28,881
somewhere in my mind

127
00:07:29,315 --> 00:07:30,783
I automatically think

128
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:31,584
it should be him.

129
00:07:32,051 --> 00:07:32,585
No one else.

130
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:34,520
I don't understand it either.

131
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,955
With a procedure like this,

132
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:36,789
Director Lin should be itching to do it.

133
00:07:37,623 --> 00:07:39,358
Why isn't he interested this time?

134
00:07:39,759 --> 00:07:40,726
But then again,

135
00:07:41,627 --> 00:07:42,762
Director Sheng's skills

136
00:07:43,029 --> 00:07:43,996
are also pretty solid.

137
00:07:44,263 --> 00:07:45,331
Of course. Of course.

138
00:07:45,431 --> 00:07:46,365
Director Sheng's technique

139
00:07:46,432 --> 00:07:47,633
is definitely not the issue.

140
00:07:47,867 --> 00:07:48,668
It's just...

141
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:51,804
you know.

142
00:07:57,944 --> 00:07:58,478
Director Lin.

143
00:07:58,911 --> 00:07:59,478
Is Du Yan's surgery

144
00:07:59,545 --> 00:08:00,680
scheduled for Thursday?

145
00:08:02,748 --> 00:08:03,282
I don't know.

146
00:08:03,916 --> 00:08:04,917
Do you know which artificial heart

147
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:06,319
Director Sheng chose?

148
00:08:08,287 --> 00:08:09,121
What does that have to do with you?

149
00:08:15,795 --> 00:08:16,629
During my first year of my doctorate,

150
00:08:16,629 --> 00:08:18,030
I suffered a serious injury.

151
00:08:19,732 --> 00:08:20,433
I spent a month

152
00:08:20,433 --> 00:08:21,133
in intensive care.

153
00:08:23,502 --> 00:08:24,837
I had saved a child,

154
00:08:27,473 --> 00:08:28,841
but the child's family

155
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:30,877
never thanked me once.

156
00:08:32,645 --> 00:08:33,412
Instead, they questioned me

157
00:08:34,247 --> 00:08:34,847
and blamed me.

158
00:08:35,548 --> 00:08:36,515
At the time,

159
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:37,517
I doubted myself completely.

160
00:08:37,783 --> 00:08:38,784
Even my faith

161
00:08:38,885 --> 00:08:39,552
in being a doctor collapsed.

162
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:41,354
Later,

163
00:08:42,755 --> 00:08:44,357
I returned to school in a daze

164
00:08:45,892 --> 00:08:46,592
and happened to sit

165
00:08:46,692 --> 00:08:48,027
in a corner of the lecture hall.

166
00:08:50,563 --> 00:08:51,797
I heard someone giving a speech.

167
00:08:54,433 --> 00:08:55,935
That person said onstage:

168
00:08:56,502 --> 00:08:58,004
Although life is full of uncertainty,

169
00:08:58,804 --> 00:08:59,572
and we can't control

170
00:08:59,572 --> 00:09:00,439
everything,

171
00:09:01,707 --> 00:09:02,575
as doctors,

172
00:09:04,277 --> 00:09:04,911
every life we save

173
00:09:06,312 --> 00:09:07,113
is one life gained.

174
00:09:11,183 --> 00:09:11,851
As a doctor,

175
00:09:12,852 --> 00:09:13,719
I firmly believe

176
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:15,788
every life we save

177
00:09:16,255 --> 00:09:16,989
is one life gained.

178
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:20,393
There are many things we can't control.

179
00:09:20,826 --> 00:09:21,928
But we must make sure

180
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:23,796
that when we face a patient,

181
00:09:24,563 --> 00:09:25,731
we give everything we have.

182
00:09:26,465 --> 00:09:27,199
When facing a case,

183
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:28,968
we must never compromise or surrender.

184
00:09:29,535 --> 00:09:30,236
When facing surgery,

185
00:09:30,269 --> 00:09:31,404
we must go all out.

186
00:09:33,105 --> 00:09:33,673
Only then,

187
00:09:34,874 --> 00:09:35,875
even if we fail in the end,

188
00:09:38,077 --> 00:09:39,845
can we remember their names

189
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:41,847
and the time we shared

190
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,284
without regret,

191
00:09:46,552 --> 00:09:47,320
and keep moving forward.

192
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:52,692
What exactly are you trying to say?

193
00:09:56,362 --> 00:09:57,763
I want you to operate on Du Yan.

194
00:10:01,033 --> 00:10:01,867
What does that have to do with me?

195
00:10:04,403 --> 00:10:05,638
That speech

196
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:07,039
made me remember

197
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,441
why I chose medicine

198
00:10:08,574 --> 00:10:09,809
and why I wanted to be a doctor.

199
00:10:10,309 --> 00:10:11,344
Have you forgotten?

200
00:10:13,479 --> 00:10:14,347
What about Zhang Diao'e?

201
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:15,948
She fell down the stairs,

202
00:10:16,048 --> 00:10:16,916
and I didn't help her up.

203
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:18,284
You tore into me.

204
00:10:18,551 --> 00:10:19,151
You said I wasn't worthy

205
00:10:19,151 --> 00:10:20,553
of wearing this white coat.

206
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:23,089
You made me realize

207
00:10:23,322 --> 00:10:24,624
that being a doctor wasn't enough.

208
00:10:25,358 --> 00:10:26,292
I also had to be

209
00:10:26,292 --> 00:10:27,426
a kind and compassionate doctor.

210
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:28,427
Back then,

211
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:29,428
if anyone treated a patient

212
00:10:29,528 --> 00:10:30,429
even slightly badly,

213
00:10:30,563 --> 00:10:31,630
you couldn't tolerate it.

214
00:10:32,031 --> 00:10:33,432
So why is this time different?

215
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,334
You know Du Yan's surgery

216
00:10:35,401 --> 00:10:35,868
needs you.

217
00:10:35,868 --> 00:10:37,003
Why are you ignoring him?

218
00:11:09,969 --> 00:11:10,870
I put the dishes in the fridge.

219
00:11:10,903 --> 00:11:11,437
Microwave them

220
00:11:11,437 --> 00:11:12,271
if you want to eat.

221
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:13,072
And there's rice

222
00:11:13,406 --> 00:11:14,173
in the rice cooker.

223
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,107
I set the timer.

224
00:11:15,975 --> 00:11:16,676
Got it.

225
00:11:17,276 --> 00:11:17,877
What did you get?

226
00:11:18,477 --> 00:11:19,311
Remember to take a nap.

227
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:20,846
Rain is forecast today.

228
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:21,647
So don't go out.

229
00:11:21,914 --> 00:11:23,649
Got it, nag.

230
00:11:24,884 --> 00:11:25,751
Bye-bye.

231
00:11:26,952 --> 00:11:28,554
Got it, nag.

232
00:11:30,589 --> 00:11:31,524
Bye-bye.

233
00:12:01,587 --> 00:12:02,521
Back then,

234
00:12:02,788 --> 00:12:03,389
if anyone treated a patient

235
00:12:03,456 --> 00:12:04,356
even slightly badly,

236
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:05,558
you couldn't tolerate it.

237
00:12:06,092 --> 00:12:07,393
So why is this time different?

238
00:12:07,726 --> 00:12:08,494
You know

239
00:12:08,894 --> 00:12:10,329
how hard I worked

240
00:12:10,529 --> 00:12:11,931
to help Du Yan regain the will to live.

241
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:13,199
I truly hope he receives

242
00:12:13,332 --> 00:12:14,867
the safest and most reliable treatment.

243
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:16,268
You're still running away.

244
00:12:18,637 --> 00:12:19,438
You haven't moved on.

245
00:12:22,708 --> 00:12:24,810
A windshield is larger

246
00:12:25,111 --> 00:12:26,112
than a rearview mirror

247
00:12:27,713 --> 00:12:29,081
because the future ahead

248
00:12:30,116 --> 00:12:31,917
matters more than the past behind.

249
00:13:07,286 --> 00:13:08,053
Du Yan's surgery—

250
00:13:08,654 --> 00:13:09,522
will you let me do it?

251
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:11,490
Why?

252
00:13:14,326 --> 00:13:15,094
Because I want to.

253
00:13:18,764 --> 00:13:19,398
Do you also think

254
00:13:19,431 --> 00:13:20,633
there's something wrong with my surgical plan?

255
00:13:22,134 --> 00:13:22,535
No.

256
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:25,771
But I think my plan

257
00:13:25,838 --> 00:13:26,472
carries less risk.

258
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:30,409
Lin Yi.

259
00:13:32,945 --> 00:13:33,679
Have I usually

260
00:13:33,679 --> 00:13:34,547
treated you too well?

261
00:13:34,947 --> 00:13:35,881
How dare you speak to me like that?

262
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:37,516
Let me tell you:

263
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,585
I'm the head of Cardiac Surgery

264
00:13:39,952 --> 00:13:41,120
and the lead surgeon for this operation.

265
00:13:41,554 --> 00:13:43,189
The surgical plan is my decision.

266
00:13:45,591 --> 00:13:45,958
Director.

267
00:13:47,927 --> 00:13:48,294
This patient...

268
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:48,894
Do you understand?

269
00:13:59,371 --> 00:13:59,772
Wait.

270
00:14:33,706 --> 00:14:34,607
Before I returned to China,

271
00:14:34,607 --> 00:14:36,041
didn't I already make it clear

272
00:14:36,175 --> 00:14:37,209
that I rejected your account?

273
00:14:37,409 --> 00:14:38,110
Why are you

274
00:14:38,110 --> 00:14:38,844
bothering Director Lin again?

275
00:14:39,011 --> 00:14:39,678
Close the account.

276
00:14:40,112 --> 00:14:41,146
Otherwise, I'll terminate

277
00:14:41,146 --> 00:14:41,914
all cooperation

278
00:14:41,947 --> 00:14:43,148
between Dongli Cardiac Surgery and your company.

279
00:14:43,482 --> 00:14:44,250
Understood. Understood.

280
00:14:44,450 --> 00:14:45,584
We're truly sorry, Director Sheng.

281
00:14:45,684 --> 00:14:46,752
We didn't think it through.

282
00:14:47,486 --> 00:14:48,854
I've handled this for you.

283
00:14:50,356 --> 00:14:52,691
That salesperson won't contact you again.

284
00:14:53,626 --> 00:14:54,960
Delete his contact information.

285
00:14:58,764 --> 00:14:59,965
I don't have his contact information.

286
00:15:02,334 --> 00:15:02,735
Get out.

287
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:08,107
Thank you, Director.

288
00:15:18,717 --> 00:15:18,984
Du Yan.

289
00:15:18,984 --> 00:15:20,486
His condition worsened again last night.

290
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:24,290
Brother.

291
00:15:25,357 --> 00:15:26,292
I've been thinking

292
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:27,559
about what Professor Zhang said.

293
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:29,762
If we could find

294
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:30,663
a kind of nanoparticle

295
00:15:30,796 --> 00:15:31,864
with high transfection efficiency,

296
00:15:32,264 --> 00:15:33,399
low toxicity,

